  "description": "Note *Not available in 3DEC . In reality, pore pressure build-up is a secondary effect, although many people seem to think it is the primary response to cyclic loading. The primary effect is the irrecoverable volume contraction of the matrix of grains when a material is taken through a complete strain cycle with the confining stress held constant. Since it is grain rearrangement rather than grain volume change that takes place, the volume of the void space decreases under constant confining stress. If the voids are filled with fluid, then the pressure of the fluid increases and the effective s",
